    <dcterms:title>I promessi sposi.&#13;
Opere di Alessando Manzoni, vol. 1</dcterms:title>
    <dcterms:description>Wikipedia page about this book: https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_promessi_sposi</dcterms:description>
    <pgterms:marc508>Produced by Giovanni Fini and the Online Distributed
Proofreading Team at http://www.pgdp.net (This file was
produced from images generously made available by The
Internet Archive/Canadian Libraries)</pgterms:marc508>
    <pgterms:marc520>"I promessi sposi" by Alessandro Manzoni is a historical novel first published between 1825 and 1827. Set in Spanish-ruled Lombardy from 1628 to 1630, it follows humble protagonists through a turbulent era marked by plague and oppression. Based on rigorous historical research, including archive documents about the nun of Monza and the 1630 plague, it became Italy's most representative Romantic work and a cornerstone of modern Italian literature, breaking tradition by centering common people rather than the powerful. (This is an automatically generated summary.)</pgterms:marc520>
    <pgterms:marc901>file:///public/vhost/g/gutenberg/html/files/45334/45334-h/images/cover.jpg</pgterms:marc901>
    <pgterms:marc908>Reading ease score: 47.8 (College-level). Difficult to read.</pgterms:marc908>
